Vice President Mike Pence led a discussion with the chief executives of approximately 50 states, territories, and the city of Washington, DC, and the White House Coronavirus Task Force to discuss local, state, and federal COVID-19 response and best practices on safely reopening America's schools. The discussion focused on addressing the holistic health and learning objectives of students. Pence discussed best practices for limiting the spread of COVID-19 while keeping America open, including adhering to state and local guidelines and wearing face coverings. They also discussed expanding testing, supporting long-term care residents, increasing healthcare capacity, and safely reopening schools. Dr. Birx discussed testing and trends, including utilizing and expanding pooled testing. The discussion also included best practices for safely reopening K-12 schools and higher education institutions in the fall, as well as an overview of CDC guidance for reopening schools. The Vice President also called on governors to encourage citizens who have recovered from COVID-19 to donate convalescent plasma.